title.rendered: Lucknow Super Giants(LSG) vs Delhi, Indian T20 League 2023: Today’s Fantasy Team, Probable Playing XIs, Pitch Report & Fantasy Tips

content.rendered:
Today’s Fantasy Team for Lucknow Super Giants(LSG) vs Delhi Match

We have opted for a fantasy cricket team on basis of probable XIs, recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable LSG & Delhi Playing XIs

LSG: KL Rahul (c & wk), Kyle Mayers*, Ayush Badoni, Deepak Hooda, Krunal Pandya, Marcus Stoinis*, Daniel Sams*, Mark Wood*, Krishnappa Gowtham/Jaydev Unadkat, Avesh Khan, Ravi Bishnoi

Delhi: David Warner* (c), Prithvi Shaw, Mitchell Marsh*, Rilee Rossouw*, Rovman Powell*, Sarfaraz Khan (wk), Axar Patel, Lalit Yadav/Kamlesh Nagarkoti, Kuldeep Yadav, Khaleel Ahmed, Chetan Sakariya

LSG vs Delhi Pitch Report

Venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow

(Based on last three T20Is)

1st innings average score: 151

2nd innings average score: 122

Wickets per innings: 6

Type: Slow

Wins

Batting 1st: 67%

Batting 2nd: 33%

Also Read:

Delhi vs Gujarat Fantasy Tips

Fantasy Tips of The Day

Axar Patel’s resurgence with the bat has made him a solid fantasy prospect. Since 2022, he has scored 392 runs at 30, scalped 31 wickets at a strike rate of 22, and pouched 15 catches.

Prithvi Shaw smashed a fifty in one of the two games against Lucknow last year. He is coming on the back of an impressive run in the 2022-23 T20 domestic season: 332 runs at 37 including a century.

KL Rahul has collected 373 runs at 31, never scoring less than 10 against Delhi. In addition, he has generated points for 10 catches.

Krunal Pandya is a tough nut to crack for Delhi bowlers, who failed to dismiss him in six of the last eight innings. Overall, he has scored 291 runs at 36, scalped 10 wickets, and pouched eight catches.

Since the last season, Kuldeep Yadav has picked 26 wickets at an impressive strike rate of 12.5 in 19 professional T20s.

All eyes will be on Mitchell Marsh, who has been a popular pick in fantasy cricket of late. Since 2021, he has maintained an average of over 30.

Ravi Bishnoi operates well in middle overs and may also be called upon at the death. In his last 10 games, he bagged 19 wickets at a strike rate of 11.8.

Mark Wood has generated a three-wicket bonus in five of the last eight T20Is, picking 19 wickets at a stunning strike rate of 8.8.

David Warner generated a 30-run bonus only once in the last 11 T20s. In two matches against Lucknow last year, he managed just seven runs.

Pacers scalped 60% of the wickets in the last three matches at the venue.
